item.description:
arXiv:2110.07104v4 Announce Type: replace-cross Abstract: We define conic reduction $X^{\mathrm{red}}_{
u}$ for torus actions on the boundary $X$ of a strictly pseudo-convex domain and for a given weight $
u$ labeling a unitary irreducible representation. There is a natural residual circle action on $X^{\mathrm{red}}_{
u}$. We have two natural decompositions of the corresponding Hardy spaces $H(X)$ and $H(X^{\mathrm{red}}_{
u})$. The first one is given by the ladder of isotypes $H(X)_{k
u}$, $k\in\mathbb{Z}$, the second one is given by the $k$-th Fourier components $H(X^{\mathrm{red}}_{
u})_k$ induced by the residual circle action. The aim of this paper is to prove that they are isomorphic for $k$ sufficiently large. The result is given for spaces of $(0,q)$-forms with $L^2$-coefficient when $X$ is a CR manifold with non-degenerate Levi-curvature.
